Archips opiparus is a species of moth of the family Tortricidae. It is found in the Chinese provinces of Guizhou, Hunan, Sichuan and Yunnan.
The length of the forewings is 8â€“10 mm for males and about 8 mm for females. The forewings are brown with a reddish-brown and dark-brown pattern. The hindwings are greyish brown, but apricot yellow at the apex.